|YK0s  A Necromancer's power over death can be molded into a deadly force.   s|XX0
|YK0s  With this ability, a Necromancer can raise an unholy creature to aid  s|XX0
|YK0s   them in combat. The simplest creature is a skeleton that will fade   s|XX0
|YK0s     over time. At guild level 5, a Necromancer can raise a combat-     s|XX0
|YK0s   oriented ghoul. Next, at guild level 8, the Necromancer can raise a  s|XX0
|YK0s    zombie. Though the zombie cannot fight, it will follow its master   s|XX0
|YK0s    and provide carrying space. At guild level 17, a Necromancer can    s|XX0
|YK0s  summon a wraith: a powerful, but temporary creature. At guild level   s|XX0
|YK0s      24, a Necromancer can summon a powerful spell-casting lich.       s|XX0
|YK0s   Finally, as the Necromancer closes on their education in the dark    s|XX0
|YK0s  arts, they have the ability to summon a ghost using the corpse of a   s|XX0
|YK0s   foe. This requires the Necromancer to be at least level 50.  Even    s|XX0
|YK0s        so, the ghost will only last a maximum of 30 minutes.           s|XX0
|YK0s                                                                        s|XX0
|YK0s  Necromancers can "feed" a corpse to their ghoul to help it regain     s|XX0
|YK0s                          some of its health.                           s|XX0
|YK0s                                                                        s|XX0
|YK0s     Each of these spells require a corpse as part of the ritual.       s|XX0
|YK0s                                                                        s|XX0
